Yeah, I think if you look at the specs for the vintage busses, they have
governors put in to keep the speeds below 60-65.  I read this as they aren't
meant to go faster for a reason.  Things do tend to get a little weird at 80
but 65-70 I am comfortable with.  I have driven thousands of miles at this
speed in my '65 and am comfortable with it.

Bryant


